-- Sonaecom, Telecom Italia: European Equity Market Preview
-- B y   J o s e p h   C i o l l i
-- 2012-05-04T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/sonaecom-telecom-italia-european-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index rose 0.1 percent to 257.53. The
 Stoxx 50 Index (SX5P)  increased less than 0.1 percent to 2,406.90. The
 Euro Stoxx 50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the
euro, declined 0.1 percent to 2,287.10.  Qiagen NV (QGEN)  : The Dutch biotechnology company
acquired Boston-based AmniSure International LLC. Qiagen said it
expects AmniSure to add about $12 million in sales over the rest
of 2012. The shares climbed 1.6 percent to 13.11 euros.  Sonaecom SGPS SA (SNC)  : The owner of Portugal’s third-
biggest mobile-phone operator said first-quarter profit rose 24
percent, as an 11 percent decline in operating costs made up for
a 6.2 percent drop in revenue. The shares decreased 1.2 percent
to 1.21 euros.  Telecom Italia SpA (TIT)  : The Italian telecommunication
company’s main investors, including  Telefonica SA (TEF)  ,
agreed on a 3.4 billion-euro financing package to help repay
loans obtained in 2007 to buy stakes in the company. Telecom
Italia’s shares gained 2.2 percent to 85 euro cents, while
Telefonica’s shares climbed 0.1 percent to 10.68 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
